    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2 under ASME V&V 40-2018. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per Table 1 minimum requirements for MRL 2. The CFD hemolysis model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in the CPB application. Decision is Accepted with no outstanding action items. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; a structured Context of Use object is not included in this profile tier — the intended-use scope is fully described in the bound Requirement (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2) and Claim (https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case) nodes.",
